theorem interior_inter_subset_interior_inter {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior A ∩ interior B ⊆ interior (A ∩ B) := by
  intro x hx
  -- The intersection of two open interiors is itself open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (interior A ∩ interior B) :=
    (isOpen_interior (A := A)).inter (isOpen_interior (A := B))
  -- This intersection is contained in `A ∩ B`.
  have hSub : (interior A ∩ interior B) ⊆ (A ∩ B) := by
    intro y hy
    exact And.intro (interior_subset hy.1) (interior_subset hy.2)
  -- Use the definition of `interior` to exhibit an open neighbourhood of `x`
  -- contained in `A ∩ B`.
  exact
    (mem_interior.2 ⟨interior A ∩ interior B, hOpen, hSub, hx⟩)

theorem interior_inter_subset_interior_intersection
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior A ∩ interior B ⊆ interior (A ∩ B) := by
  -- `interior A ∩ interior B` is open because it is the intersection of two open sets.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (interior A ∩ interior B) := by
    have hA : IsOpen (interior A) := isOpen_interior
    have hB : IsOpen (interior B) := isOpen_interior
    exact hA.inter hB
  -- Every point of `interior A ∩ interior B` belongs to `A ∩ B`.
  have hSub : interior A ∩ interior B ⊆ A ∩ B := by
    intro x hx
    exact And.intro (interior_subset hx.1) (interior_subset hx.2)
  -- Apply `interior_maximal` to upgrade the inclusion.
  exact interior_maximal hOpen hSub

theorem interior_inter_eq_left_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    interior (A ∩ B) = A ∩ interior B := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  · -- `interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ A ∩ interior B`
    intro x hx
    have hAB : x ∈ A ∩ B := interior_subset hx
    have hxA : x ∈ A := hAB.1
    have hxIntB : x ∈ interior B :=
      (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hx
    exact And.intro hxA hxIntB
  · -- `A ∩ interior B ⊆ interior (A ∩ B)`
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxA, hxIntB⟩
    rcases (mem_interior.1 hxIntB) with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsubB⟩
    let V : Set X := U ∩ A
    have hVopen : IsOpen V := hUopen.inter hA
    have hxV : x ∈ V := And.intro hxU hxA
    have hVsub : V ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      have hyU : y ∈ U := hy.1
      have hyA : y ∈ A := hy.2
      have hyB : y ∈ B := hUsubB hyU
      exact And.intro hyA hyB
    have : x ∈ interior (A ∩ B) := by
      apply mem_interior.2
      exact ⟨V, hVopen, hxV, hVsub⟩
    exact this

theorem closure_interior_eq_of_clopen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hAopen : IsOpen A) (hAclosed : IsClosed A) :
    closure (interior A) = A := by
  have hInt : interior A = A := hAopen.interior_eq
  have hCl : closure A = A := hAclosed.closure_eq
  calc
    closure (interior A) = closure A := by
      simpa [hInt]
    _ = A := hCl
